Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Spread the @McCain Home Chips{400%g} on a #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle
with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. When the oven
is hot, bake on the top shelf, ~{25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, drain the @Sweetcorn{160%g} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, add the
sweetcorn and cook until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Adjust the heat if necessary.
Stir only twice during this time - you want the sweetcorn to pick up some nice
colour.

While the sweetcorn fries, sandwich each @British Chicken Breasts{2} between two
pieces of baking paper or cling film. Pop onto a #board{}, then give it a bash
with a #rolling pin{} or the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 1-2cm thick.

Put the @Plain Flour{1%tbsp} in a #bowl{} with a good pinch of salt and some
pepper and mix together.

Lay your chicken breast in the bowl, then toss to ensure the chicken gets an
even coating of flour. Repeat for the other breast(s). IMPORTANT: Wash your hands
and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Once the sweetcorn is charred, transfer to another medium bowl. Give the pan a
quick wipe out.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in the (now empty) frying pan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay in the chicken. Fry until golden brown and cooked through,
~{5-6%minutes} on each side. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink
in the middle.

While the chicken fries, pop a small #saucepan{} on medium heat (no oil).

Add the @Gochujang Paste{50%g}, @Honey{15%g} and @Water for the Sauce{50%ml}.
Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{4-5%minutes}.

> If your honey has hardened, put the sachet in a bowl of hot water for 1 min
> to loosen.

Once thickened, vigorously stir in the @Unsalted Butter{30%g} until melted.
Simmer for ~{1%minute} more, then remove from the heat.

While the sauce simmers, thinly slice the @Spring Onion{2}. Grate the
@Mature Cheddar Cheese{40%g}.

When the chips have 5 mins remaining, sprinkle over the cheese and return to the
oven until melted.

When everything's nearly ready, add the @Coleslaw Mix{120%g}, @Wild Rocket{40%g}
and @Mayonnaise{64%g} to the bowl of sweetcorn. Season with salt and pepper and
stir to combine.

Once the chicken is cooked, transfer to a board and cut into 2cm thick slices.

Transfer the chicken to your serving plates. Drizzle over the gochujang butter
sauce (stir well to combine again and reheat if needed).

Serve the chips and slaw on the side.

Sprinkle the sliced spring onion over the chicken to finish. Enjoy!